# Asset Fee__c Flowchart
 
```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A1[Quote or Bind Journey<br/>Asset context] --> B1[OmniScript or UI inserts Fee__c<br/>NB or MTA]
    B1 --> C1[TA_Fee_ConvertFeeAmount<br/>beforeInsert or beforeUpdate]
    C1 --> D1[Normalize Fee_Amount__c<br/>from Quote_Fee_Amount__c]
 
    D1 --> E1{Asset workflow branch}
 
    E1 -->|Quote clone| F1[CloneQuoteRelatedChildRecords.cloneFeeRecords]
    F1 --> G1[Clone Fee__c rows to cloned quote]
 
    E1 -->|Standard cancellation| H1[CancelPolicy_NewVersion OS
calls CloneFeeRecords.processFeeRecords]
    H1 --> I1{Option}
    I1 -->|Fetch| J1[Check existing fees]
    I1 -->|Clone| K1[Clone fees as returns
negate Fee_Amount__c and Quote_Fee_Amount__c
Transaction_Type__c = Cancellation
Category__c = Return]
 
    E1 -->|Cancel and Reissue| L1[CreateTransactionLineItem.UpdateTaxJur
Scenario = CancelAndReissuePolicy]
    L1 --> M1[Tax return updates + fee clones by submission
fee clones marked as cancellation return]
 
    G1 --> N1[CalculatePremiumShare.createPremiumShares]
    K1 --> N1
    M1 --> N1
 
    N1 --> O1[FeeShareProcessor.insertFeeShares]
    O1 --> P1[Fee_Share__c rows for Paid/Written]
 
    P1 --> Q1[Asset reporting and UI totals
PolicySummaryLWCController
bookofBusinessController]
 
    R1[Validation: FeeReadOnlyForAsset] -. create/update blocked when submission locked .-> B1
 
    classDef asset fill:#e9f2ff,stroke:#0b5cab,stroke-width:2px,color:#0a2d5e;
    classDef shared fill:#fff4e6,stroke:#e07a00,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#6b3d00;
    classDef decision fill:#fff8d6,stroke:#7a5d00,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#3d2f00;
    classDef guard fill:#f3e8ff,stroke:#6d28d9,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#3b1a7a;
 
    class A1,B1,F1,G1,H1,I1,J1,K1 asset;
    class C1,D1,L1,M1,N1,O1,P1,Q1 shared;
    class E1 decision;
    class R1 guard;
 
    linkStyle 0,4,5,6,7,8,9 stroke:#0b5cab,stroke-width:2px;
    linkStyle 1,2,3,10,11,12,13,14 stroke:#e07a00,stroke-width:2px;
    linkStyle 15 stroke:#6d28d9,stroke-width:2px,stroke-dasharray: 6 4;
    linkStyle 16,17 stroke:#b42318,stroke-width:2.5px;
```
 
 
